<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the organization of the transport market is one of the necessary preconditions for the implementation of the common transport policy which is provided for in the Treaty; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: transpordituru korraldamine on asutamislepingus s&auml;testatud &uuml;hise transpordipoliitika rakendamiseks vajalik eeltingimus; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the adoption of measures designed to coordinate the conditions for access to the occupation of carrier is likely to encourage the achievement of freedom to provide services and the effective exercise of the right of establishment; </inglise>
<eesti> veoettev&otilde;tja tegevusalale juurdep&auml;&auml;sutingimuste koordineerimiseks kavandatavate meetmete vastuv&otilde;tmine soodustab t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt teenuste osutamise vabaduse saavutamist ja asutamis&otilde;iguse t&otilde;husat kasutamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas provision must be made for the introduction of common rules governing access to the occupation of carrier of goods by waterway in national and international transport in order to improve the level of qualifications of carriers; whereas such improvement is likely to help towards putting the market on a sounder footing, eliminating structural excess capacities and improving the quality of the service provided, in the interests of users, carriers and the economy as a whole; </inglise>
<eesti> veoettev&otilde;tjate kvalifikatsiooni t&otilde;stmiseks tuleb s&auml;testada &uuml;histe eeskirjade kasutuselev&otilde;tmine juurdep&auml;&auml;su kohta veeteekaubaveo-ettev&otilde;tja tegevusalale siseriiklikus ja rahvusvahelises veonduses; t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt aitab selline arendamine turule kindlamale alusele, k&otilde;rvaldades liigse struktuurilise v&otilde;imsuse ning parandades osutatavate teenuste kvaliteeti kasutajate, veoettev&otilde;tjate ja kogu majanduse huvides; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas satisfactory results have been obtained through the implementation of Council Directive 74/561/EEC of 12 November 1974 on admission to the occupation of road haulage operator in national and international transport operations (4) and Council Directive 77/796/EEC of 12 December 1977 aiming at the mutual recognition of diplomas, certificates and other evidence of formal qualifications for goods haulage operators and road passenger transport operators, including measures intended to encourage these operators effectively to exercise their right to freedom of establishment (5); </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu 12. novembri 1974. aasta direktiivi 74/561/EM&Uuml; (siseriiklike ja rahvusvaheliste vedude maanteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja tegevusalale lubamise kohta) (4) ja n&otilde;ukogu 12. detsembri 1977. aasta direktiivi 77/796/EM&Uuml; (maanteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjate ja reisijate autoveo-ettev&otilde;tjate diplomite, tunnistuste ja muude ametlike kvalifikatsioonit&otilde;endite vastastikuse tunnustamise kohta ning k&otilde;nealustel ettev&otilde;tjatel asutamisvabaduse &otilde;iguse t&otilde;husa kasutamise soodustamise kohta) (5) rakendamise tulemused on olnud rahuldavad; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the rules governing access to the occupation of carrier of goods by waterway should therefore cover at least the professional competence of the carrier; whereas Member States may also maintain or lay down rules governing the good repute and financial standing of the carrier; </inglise>
<eesti> veeteekaubaveo-ettev&otilde;tja tegevusalale juurdep&auml;&auml;su eeskirjad peaksid h&otilde;lmama v&auml;hemalt veoettev&otilde;tja ametialast p&auml;devust; liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad s&auml;ilitada v&otilde;i s&auml;testada eeskirjad veoettev&otilde;tja hea maine ja rahandusliku seisukorra kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, however, there is no need to include in the common rules laid down by this Directive certain transport activities with a minor economic impact and whereas transport on own account is by definition excluded from these rules; whereas it also seems appropriate to provide for the possible exclusion from the scope of this Directive of carriers operating exclusively on navigable waterways within their territory not linked to the waterway network of another Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga kehtestatud &uuml;histesse eeskirjadesse ei ole vaja kaasata majanduslikult ebaolulisi vedusid ning omal kulul tehtavad veod v&auml;listab juba m&auml;&auml;ratlus; ilmselt on vaja s&auml;testada nende veoettev&otilde;tjate v&otilde;imalik v&auml;ljaarvamine k&auml;esoleva direktiivi reguleerimisalast, kes tegutsevad ainult oma territooriumi laevatatavatel veeteedel, mis ei ole &uuml;henduses teise liikmesriigi veeteede v&otilde;rgustikuga; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas there is a need for mutual recognition of diplomas, certificates and other evidence of formal qualifications for the activities covered by this Directive, in order to promote the effective exercise of the right of establishment; </inglise>
<eesti> asutamis&otilde;iguse t&otilde;husa kasutamise edendamiseks on vaja vastastikku tunnustada k&auml;esoleva direktiivi tegevusvaldkondade diplomeid, tunnistusi ja muid ametlikke kvalifikatsioonit&otilde;endeid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the certificate of professional competence issued pursuant to the provisions of this Directive regarding access to the occupation of carrier must be recognized as sufficient proof by the host Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> veoettev&otilde;tja tegevusalale juurdep&auml;&auml;suga seoses peab vastuv&otilde;ttev liikmesriik tunnustama piisava t&otilde;endina k&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tete alusel v&auml;ljaantud ametialase p&auml;devuse tunnistust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Member States which impose on their own nationals certain requirements as to good repute and financial standing must recognize the productinon of appropriate documents issued by a competent authority in the carrier's State of origin or prior establishment as sufficient evidence in respect of nationals of other Member States; </inglise>
<eesti> liikmesriigid, kes kehtestavad oma kodanike suhtes teatud n&otilde;udeid hea maine ja rahalise seisukorra kohta, peavad teiste liikmesriikide kodanike puhul tunnustama piisava t&otilde;endina veoettev&otilde;tja p&auml;ritoluriigi v&otilde;i eelneva tegutsemisriigi p&auml;deva asutuse v&auml;ljastatud asjakohaseid dokumente; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, further, this Directive must also apply to employed persons covered by Council Regulation (EEC) No 1612/68 of 15 October 1968 on freedom of movement for workers within the Community (1), if the Member States make access to the occupation covered by this Directive or the exercise thereof by such persons conditional on the possession of professional knowledge and skills, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevat direktiivi peab kohaldama ka t&ouml;&ouml;tajate suhtes, kes on h&otilde;lmatud n&otilde;ukogu 15. oktoobri 1968 m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1612/68 t&ouml;&ouml;tajate liikumisvabaduse kohta &uuml;henduses (1), kui liikmesriigid teevad k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga kaetud tegevusalale juurdep&auml;&auml;su v&otilde;i sellel tegutsemise s&otilde;ltuvaks ametialastest teadmistest ja oskustest, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> CHAPTER I </inglise>
<eesti> I PEAT&Uuml;KK </eesti>
<inglise> Definitions and scope </inglise>
<eesti> M&otilde;isted ja reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Access to the occupation of carrier of goods by waterway in national and international transport shall be governed by the provisions adopted by the Member States pursuant to the common rules laid down in this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Juurdep&auml;&auml;su veeteekaubaveo-ettev&otilde;tja tegevusalale siseriiklikus ja rahvusvahelises veonduses reguleeritakse k&auml;esolevas direktiivis kehtestatud &uuml;histe eeskirjade alusel liikmesriikide vastuv&otilde;etud s&auml;tetega. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Directive: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> - 'occupation of carrier of goods by waterway vessel' means the activities engaged in by any natural person or any undertaking carrying goods by inland waterway for hire or reward, even if this occupation is not exercised on a regular basis, </inglise>
<eesti> - veeteekaubaveo-ettev&otilde;tja tegevusala - mis tahes f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tja tegevus, kes veab kaupu siseveeteedel rendi v&otilde;i tasu eest, isegi kui see tegevus ei toimu regulaarselt, </eesti>
<inglise> - 'undertaking' means companies or firms within the meaning of Article 58 of the Treaty and groups or cooperatives of operators whose purpose is to obtain business from shipping agents for distribution among their members, irrespective of whether such groups or cooperatives possess legal personality. </inglise>
<eesti> - ettev&otilde;tja - &auml;ri&uuml;hingud asutamislepingu artikli 58 t&auml;henduses ja ettev&otilde;tjate r&uuml;hmad v&otilde;i &uuml;histud, kelle eesm&auml;rk on saada ekspediitoritelt oma liikmetele t&ouml;&ouml;d, olenemata sellest, kes need r&uuml;hmad ja &uuml;histud on juriidilised isikud v&otilde;i mitte. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive shall not apply to natural persons or undertakings pursuing the occupation of carrier of goods by waterway using vessels with a deadweight capacity at maximum draft not exceeding 200 tonnes. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat direktiivi ei kohaldata veeteekaubaveo-ettev&otilde;tja tegevusalal tegutsevate f&uuml;&uuml;siliste isikute ega ettev&otilde;tjate suhtes, kes kasutavad laevu, mille dedveit maksimaalse s&uuml;vise juures ei &uuml;leta 200 tonni. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may lower this limit for all or some transport operations or certain categories of transport. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad k&otilde;igi v&otilde;i m&otilde;ne veo v&otilde;i teatud veokategooriate puhul seda m&auml;&auml;ra v&auml;hendada. </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive shall likewise not apply to natural persons or undertakings operating ferries. </inglise>
<eesti> Samuti ei kohaldata k&auml;esolevat direktiivi parvlaevadeliikluses tegutsevate f&uuml;&uuml;siliste isikute ega ettev&otilde;tjate suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> CHAPTER II </inglise>
<eesti> II PEAT&Uuml;KK </eesti>
<inglise> Access to the occupation </inglise>
<eesti> Juurdep&auml;&auml;s tegevusalale </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Natural persons or undertakings wishing to pursue the occupation of carrier of goods by waterway must satisfy the condition of professional competence, even if they are members of a group or cooperative of operators within the meaning of Article 1 (2) or exercise their occupation exclusively for a specific period of time as subcontractors to another waterway transport undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti> F&uuml;&uuml;silised isikud v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tjad, kes soovivad tegelda veeteekaubaveo-ettev&otilde;tja tegevusalal, peavad t&auml;itma ametialase p&auml;devuse tingimust isegi siis, kui nad on ettev&otilde;tjate r&uuml;hma v&otilde;i &uuml;histu liikmed artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 2 t&auml;henduses v&otilde;i kui nad tegelevad sellel tegevusalal teise veeteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja allt&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;tjana ainult kindla aja jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise> If the applicant is a natural person who does not satisfy that condition, the competent authorities may nevertheless authorize him to pursue the occupation of carrier of goods by waterway provided that he indicates to them another person satisfying the condition who in actual fact manages the transport operations on a permanent basis. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui taotleja on f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik, kes seda tingimust ei t&auml;ida, v&otilde;ib p&auml;dev asutus sellegipoolest lubada tal tegelda veeteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja tegevusalal, kui ta n&auml;itab neile teist isikut, kes tingimust t&auml;idab ja tegelikult veooperatsioone alaliselt juhib. </eesti>
<inglise> If the applicant is an undertaking within the meaning of Article 1 (2) one of the natural persons who in actual fact manage the undertaking's transport operations on a permanent basis must meet the condition of professional competence. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui taotleja on ettev&otilde;tja artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 2 t&auml;henduses, peab f&uuml;&uuml;silistest isikutest &uuml;ks, kes ettev&otilde;tja veooperatsioone tegelikult alaliselt juhib, t&auml;itma ametialase p&auml;devuse tingimust. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The condition of professional competence shall consist in the possession of the standard of competence accepted by the authority or body appointed for this purpose by each Member State in the subjects listed in the Annex. </inglise>
<eesti> Ametialase p&auml;devuse tingimus on lisas loetletud ainevaldkondades sellise p&auml;devuse omamine, nagu seda aktsepteerib iga liikmesriigi selleks nimetatud asutus v&otilde;i organ. </eesti>
<inglise> The necessary knowledge shall be acquired either by attending courses or by practical experience in a waterway transport undertaking, or by a combination of the two. </inglise>
<eesti> Vajalikud teadmised saadakse kursustel v&otilde;i veeteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja saadud praktilistest kogemustest v&otilde;i nende m&otilde;lema abil. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may exempt the holders of certain diplomas from providing evidence of their knowledge of the subjects listed in the Annex which are covered by the said diplomas. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad teatud diplomiga isikud vabastada t&otilde;endite esitamisest oma teadmiste kohta lisas loetletud ainevaldkondades, mida nimetatud diplomid h&otilde;lmavad. </eesti>
<inglise> After verifying possession of the knowledge concerned, the authority or body referred to in the first subparagraph shall issue a certificate. </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;rast asjaomaste teadmiste t&otilde;endamist annab esimeses l&otilde;igus nimetatud asutus v&otilde;i organ v&auml;lja tunnistuse. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> A Member State may, after consulting the Commission, exempt from application of this Directive carriers operating exclusively on navigable waterways within their territory not linked to the waterway network of another Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Olles konsulteerinud komisjoniga v&otilde;ib liikmesriik v&auml;lja arvata k&auml;esoleva direktiivi reguleerimisalast need veoettev&otilde;tjad, kes tegutsevad ainult oma territooriumi laevatatavatel veeteedel, mis ei ole &uuml;henduses teise liikmesriigi veeteede v&otilde;rgustikuga. </eesti>
<inglise> Practical experience gained in a transport undertaking exempted from application of these conditions shall not give entitlement to the certificate referred to in paragraph 2. </inglise>
<eesti> Nende tingimuste kohaldamisest vabastatud veoettev&otilde;tja saadud praktilised kogemused ei anna &otilde;igust l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud tunnistusele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall lay down the terms on which a transport undertaking may, by way of derogation from Article 3 (1), operate on a provisional basis for a maximum of one year, which period may be extended by not more than six months in special duly justified cases, in the event of the death or physical or legal incapacity of the natural person pursuing the occupation of carrier or the natural person complying with the provisions of Article 3. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid s&auml;testavad tingimused, mille alusel veoettev&otilde;tja tegevusalal tegeleva f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku v&otilde;i artikli 3 s&auml;tetele vastava f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku surma v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse v&otilde;i teov&otilde;imetuse korral v&otilde;ib veoettev&otilde;tja erandina artikli 3 l&otilde;ikest 1 tegutseda ajutiselt maksimaalselt &uuml;he aasta, mida v&otilde;ib erilistel n&otilde;uetekohaselt p&otilde;hjendatud juhtudel pikendada kuni kuue kuu v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> However, the competent authorities of the Member States may, by way of exception, permanently authorize in certain special cases the operation of an undertaking by a person who does not meet the condition of professional competence referred to in Article 3, but who has had at least three years' practical experience in the everyday management of the undertaking concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Erandina v&otilde;ivad liikmesriikide p&auml;devad asutused teatud erijuhtudel lubada ettev&otilde;tjat alaliselt juhtida isikul, kes ei t&auml;ida artiklis 3 nimetatud ametialase p&auml;devuse tingimust, kuid kellel on k&otilde;nealuse ettev&otilde;tja igap&auml;evases juhtimises v&auml;hemalt kolmeaastane praktiline kogemus. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Natural persons who provide proof that before 1 July 1990 they legally pursued in a Member State the occupation of carrier of goods by waterway in national or international transport shall, for the purposes of obtaining the certificate referred to in Article 3 (2), be exempt from the obligation to prove that they meet the conditions laid down therein. </inglise>
<eesti> F&uuml;&uuml;silised isikud, kes t&otilde;endavad, et enne 1. juulit 1990 tegelesid nad liikmesriigis seaduslikult veeteekaubaveo-ettev&otilde;tja tegevusalal siseriiklikus v&otilde;i rahvusvahelises veonduses, vabastatakse artikli 3 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud tunnistuse saamiseks selles s&auml;testatud tingimuste t&otilde;endamiskohustusest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Reasons must be given for any decision rejecting an application for access to the occupation of carrier of goods by waterway taken by the competent authorities of the Member States pursuant to the measures adopted on the basis of this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi alusel vastuv&otilde;etud meetmete kohaselt peavad liikmesriikide p&auml;devad asutused p&otilde;hjendama k&otilde;iki oma otsuseid, kui nad l&uuml;kkavad tagasi veeteekaubaveo-ettev&otilde;tja tegevusalale juurdep&auml;&auml;su taotluse. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that the competent authorities withdraw an authorization to pursue the occupation of carrier of goods by waterway if they find that the conditions laid down in Article 3 are no longer met, subject to allowing, where appropriate, sufficient time for the recruitment of a replacement. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid tagavad, et p&auml;devad asutused t&uuml;histavad tegevusloa veeteekaubaveo-ettev&otilde;tja tegevusalal, kui nad leiavad, et artiklis 3 kehtestatud tingimused ei ole enam t&auml;idetud, andes vajaduse korral piisavalt aega asendaja leidmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that the natural persons and undertakings referred to in this Directive have the opportunity to defend their interests by appropriate means with regard to the decisions referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid tagavad, et l&otilde;ikes 1 ja 2 nimetatud otsustega seoses on k&auml;esolevas direktiivis nimetatud f&uuml;&uuml;silistel isikutel ja ettev&otilde;tjatel v&otilde;imalus kohaste vahenditega kaitsta oma huve. </eesti>
<inglise> CHAPTER III </inglise>
<eesti> III PEAT&Uuml;KK </eesti>
<inglise> Mutual recognition of diplomas, certificates and other evidence of formal qualifications </inglise>
<eesti> Diplomite, tunnistuste ja muude ametlike kvalifikatsioonit&otilde;endite vastastikune tunnustamine </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall recognize the certificates referred to in the second subparagraph of Article 3 (2) which have been issued by another Member State as sufficient proof of professional competence. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid tunnustavad artikli 3 l&otilde;ike 2 teises l&otilde;igus nimetatud teise liikmesriigi v&auml;ljaantud tunnistusi ametialase p&auml;devuse piisava t&otilde;endina. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where a Member State imposes on its own nationals certain requirements as to good repute or absence of bankruptcy, that State shall accept as sufficient evidence in respect of nationals of other Member States, without prejudice to paragraphs 2 and 3, an extract from a judicial record or, failing that, an equivalent document issued by a competent judicial or administrative authority in the carrier's country of origin or prior establishment showing that these conditions have been met. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriik kehtestab oma kodanike suhtes teatud n&otilde;uded seoses hea maine v&otilde;i maksuj&otilde;ulisusega, peab see riik, ilma et see piiraks l&otilde;igete 2 ja 3 kohaldamist, aktsepteerima piisava t&otilde;endina teiste liikmesriikide kodanike puhul v&auml;ljav&otilde;tet karistusregistrist v&otilde;i selle puudumisel samav&auml;&auml;rset dokumenti, mille on v&auml;ljastanud veoettev&otilde;tja p&auml;ritoluriigi v&otilde;i eelneva tegutsemisriigi p&auml;dev kohtuorgan v&otilde;i haldusasutus ning mis n&auml;itab, et asjakohased tingimused on t&auml;idetud. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Where a Member State imposes on its own nationals certain requirements as to good repute, and proof that such requirements are met cannot be furnished by means of the document referred to in paragraph 1, that State shall accept as sufficient evidence in respect of nationals of other Member States a certificate issued by a competent judicial or administrative authority in the State of origin or prior establishment stating that the requirements in question have been met. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriik kehtestab oma kodanike suhtes teatud n&otilde;uded seoses hea mainega ja kui k&otilde;nealuste n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmist ei saa t&otilde;endada l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud dokumendi abil, peab see riik aktsepteerima piisava t&otilde;endina teiste liikmesriikide kodanike puhul tunnistust, mille on v&auml;ljastanud p&auml;ritoluriigi v&otilde;i eelneva tegutsemisriigi p&auml;dev kohtuorgan v&otilde;i haldusasutus ning mis kinnitab, et asjakohased tingimused on t&auml;idetud. </eesti>
<inglise> Such certificates shall relate to the specific facts regarded as relevant by the host State. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealused tunnistused peavad sisaldama konkreetseid andmeid, mida vastuv&otilde;ttev riik peab asjakohaseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the document required in accordance with paragraphs 1 and 2 is not issued by the State of origin or prior establishment, such document may be replaced by a declaration on oath or by a solemn declaration made by the person concerned before a competent judicial or administrative authority or, where appropriate, a notary in that person's State of origin or prior establishment; such authority or notary shall issue a certificate attesting the authenticity of the declaration on oath or solemn declaration. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui p&auml;ritoluriik v&otilde;i eelnev tegutsemisriik ei ole vastavalt l&otilde;igetele 1 ja 2 n&otilde;utavat dokumenti v&auml;ljastatud, v&otilde;ib selle dokumendi asendada vandet&otilde;otusega v&otilde;i p&uuml;haliku t&otilde;otusega, mille asjaomane isik annab oma p&auml;ritoluriigi v&otilde;i eelneva tegutsemisriigi kohtuorgani v&otilde;i haldusasutuse v&otilde;i vajaduse korral notari ees. Selline asutus v&otilde;i notar t&otilde;endab vandet&otilde;otuse v&otilde;i p&uuml;haliku t&otilde;otuse &otilde;igsust. </eesti>
<inglise> The declaration in respect of bankruptcy may likewise be made before a competent professional body in the same State. </inglise>
